The Bay Area and California can’t afford to reopen without contact tracers, public health experts said.
Even after they return to their day jobs, they will be available to do contact tracing as needed, she said.
“Contact tracing in the context of a pandemic only makes sense with all these other community mitigation measures in place,” Peddycord said.
Singapore, for instance, demonstrated how effective contact tracing can be, said Dr. Dan Diekema, director of infectious diseases at the University of Iowa.
Apple and Google last week said they would build functions to their smartphones that could be used for contact tracing.